glo-Catholic.<ref>http://www.ascensionchicago.org/about</ref><ref name=\"ascensionchicago.org\">http://www.ascensionchicago.org/worship/worship-overview</ref><ref>Giles, George C. ''History of the Church of the Ascension, Chicago, Illinois 1857-1982.'' North Plains Press, 1984, http://anglicanhistory.org/usa/ascension_chicago_giles/10.html.</ref> Solemn High Mass on Sundays and Holy Days; monthly Evensong with Benediction of the Blessed Sacrament (October through May); monthly Holy Rosary throughout the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ascensionchicago.org/worship|title=Worship - Church of the Ascension Episcopal - Chicago, IL}}</ref><ref name=\"ascensionchicago.org\"/> Chanted minor propers in Latin.<ref>http://www.ascensionchicago.org/tags/minor-propers</ref>\n|\n|-\n|St. Anna's Church\n|[[New Orleans, Louisiana]]\n|\n| Self Identification as Anglo-Catholic, Weekly Rosary, Cell of the Holy House of Our Lady of Walsingham <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stannanola.org/|title=Saint Anna's Episcopal Church New Orleans|website=www.stannanola.org}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| Grace and St Peter's Church\n| [[Baltimore|Baltimore, Maryland]]\n|\n| Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://graceandstpeter.org/home|title=Grace and St. Peter's Church - An Episcopal Church in the Anglo-Catholic Tradition &#124; Home|first=Grace and St Peter's Church-An Episcopal Church in the Anglo-Catholic|last=Tradition|website=graceandstpeter.org}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| Church of the Advent\n| [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n|\n| Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theadventboston.org/|title=Home Page|website=The Church of the Advent}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| All Saints, Ashmont\n| [[Dorchester, Massachusetts]]\n|\n| Self identifies as Anglo-Catholic\n|\n|-\n|The Parish of the Good Shepherd\n|[[Newton, Massachusetts]]\n|\n|Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic, known as \"the High Church of the western Suburbs\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.goodshepherdnewton.org/worship|title=Worship|website=www.goodshepherdnewton.org|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> \n|\n|-\n|St. John's Church\n|Detroit, Michigan\n|[[File:St. John Episcopal Church Detroit.jpg|frameless]]\n|Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic. Rector is SSC.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stjohnsdetroit.org/rector.htm|title=Rector - St. John's Episcopal Church of Detroit|website=stjohnsdetroit.org|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref> Daily Masses use the Anglican Missal. Sundays Masses use the 1928 Prayer Book.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stjohnsdetroit.org/about.htm|title=About Us - St. John's Episcopal Church of Detroit|website=stjohnsdetroit.org|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref> Exposition and benediction of the Blessed Sacrament on Thursdays.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stjohnsdetroit.org/cbs.htm|title=The Confraternity of the Blessed Sacrament - St. John's Episcopal Church of Detroit|website=stjohnsdetroit.org|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref> Celebrates all major feasts.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://stjohnsdetroit.org/cgi-bin/Calcium?CalendarName=Parish&Op=ShowIt|title=Calcium - St. John's Episcopal Church Calendar|website=stjohnsdetroit.org|access-date=2019-03-21}}</ref> Shrine of Our Lady of Walsingham.   \n|\n|-\n|St. Luke's Anglican\n|[[Corinth, Mississippi]]\n|\n| Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mychurchwebsite.net/|title=MyChurchWebsite.net &#124; Church Websites &#124; Website Builder|website=mychurchwebsite.net}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|St. Mary's, Kansas City\n|[[Kansas City, Missouri]]\n|[[File:St. Mary's Episcopal Church, Kansas City.jpg|frameless]]\n|Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.stmaryskcmo.org/|title=Saint Mary's Episcopal Church|website=Saint Mary's Episcopal Church|language=en|access-date=2018-07-20}}</ref> Solemn High Mass on Sundays and holy days, chanted minor propers in English, Exposition of the Blessed Sacrament on Wednesday evenings, Benediction on certain Holy Days, Marian antiphon sung after High Mass.\n|NRHP-listed in 19