ies as \"a small, traditional, Anglo-Catholic parish,\" in the once predominantly Anglo-Catholic diocese of Northern Indiana.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ednin.org/employment/st-pauls-laporte|title=St. Paul's (LaPorte)|website=Episcopal Diocese of Northern Indiana|language=en-US|access-date=2020-02-12}}</ref> \n|\n|-\n|[[Church of the Ascension, Chicago]]\n|[[Chicago, Illinois]] \n|\n|Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic.<ref>http://www.ascensionchicago.org/about</ref><ref name=\"ascensionchicago.org\">http://www.ascensionchicago.org/worship/worship-overview</ref><ref>Giles, George C. ''History of the Church of the Ascension, Chicago, Illinois 1857-1982.'' North Plains Press, 1984, http://anglicanhistory.org/usa/ascension_chicago_giles/10.html.</ref> Solemn High Mass on Sundays and Holy Days; monthly Evensong with Benediction of the Blessed Sacrament (October through May); monthly Holy Rosary throughout the year.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ascensionchicago.org/worship|title=Worship - Church of the Ascension Episcopal - Chicago, IL}}</ref><ref name=\"ascensionchicago.org\"/> Chanted minor propers in Latin.<ref>http://www.ascensionchicago.org/tags/minor-propers</ref>\n|\n|-\n|St. Anna's Church\n|[[New Orleans, Louisiana]]\n|\n| Self Identification as Anglo-Catholic, Weekly Rosary, Cell of the Holy House of Our Lady of Walsingham <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.stannanola.org/|title=Saint Anna's Episcopal Church New Orleans|website=www.stannanola.org}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| Grace and St Peter's Church\n| [[Baltimore|Baltimore, Maryland]]\n|\n| Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://graceandstpeter.org/home|title=Grace and St. Peter's Church - An Episcopal Church in the Anglo-Catholic Tradition &#124; Home|first=Grace and St Peter's Church-An Episcopal Church in the Anglo-Catholic|last=Tradition|website=graceandstpeter.org}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n| Church of the Advent\n| [[Boston, Massachusetts]]\n|\n| Self-identifies as Anglo-Catholic.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https: