{"title_page": "Japie Mulder", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Use South African English|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox rugby biography\n|                   name = \n|                  image =\n|                caption = \n|              birth_name = \n|               nickname = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1969|10|18}}\n| birth_place = [[Springs, South Africa|Springs]], [[South Africa]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.84}}\n| weight = 84 kg (13 st 3 lb; 185 lb)\n|            ru_position = [[Centre (rugby union)|Centre]]\n|        ru_amateuryears = \n|        ru_amateurclubs = \n|            ru_amupdate = \n|        ru_nationalteam = [[South Africa national rugby union team|South Africa]]\n|       ru_nationalyears = 1994-2001\n|        ru_nationalcaps = 34\n|      ru_nationalpoints = (35)\n|            ru_ntupdate = 26 June 2015\n|           ru_clubyears = \n|            ru_proclubs =\n|            ru_clubcaps = \n|          ru_clubpoints = \n|          ru_clubupdate = \n|                super14 = \n|           super14years = \n|            super14caps =  \n|          super14points = \n|         ru_currentclub = \n|          super14update = \n|            ru_province =\n|       ru_provinceyears = \n|        ru_provincecaps = \n|      ru_provincepoints = \n|      ru_provinceupdate =\n|             occupation = Professional rugby union footballer \n|                 spouse = \n|               children = \n|                 school = \n|             university = \n}}\n\n'''Jacobus Cornelius Mulder''', better known as '''Japie Mulder''' (born 18 October 1969 in Springs, [[South Africa]]), is a former [[South Africa]]n [[rugby union]] player who played for the [[South Africa national rugby union team]] between [[1994 in sports|1994]] and [[2001 in sports|2001]].\n\nHe played as a centre: {{height|m=1.80}} and {{cvt|77|kg}}.\n\nHe is now an employee of the telecommunications infrastructure company, Dark Fibre Africa (Pty) Ltd.\n\nIn 2007 he pleaded guilty to the indecent assault and attempted rape of a South African schoolgirl who was the daughter of a close friend.<ref name=\"mandg\">{{cite web|url=http://www.mg.co.za/article/2007-11-29-japie-mulder-pleads-guilty-to-indecent-assault|title=Japie Mulder pleads guilty to indecent assault|date=29 November 2007|work=Mail & Guardian|accessdate=2009-04-27}}</ref>\n\nOn 29 December 2009, Mulder and his wife and children were hijacked in the [[East Rand]]. Mulder was forced into the [[Trunk (automobile)|boot]] in the car, while his hijackers stole money from his bank account.<ref name=\"mandh\">{{cite web |url= http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Nightmare-hijacking-for-ex-Bok-20091230 |title= Nightmare hijacking for ex-Bok |date= 30 December 2009 |work= News24}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n\n===Provincial===\n* [[Transvaal Province|Transvaal]] until 1995\n* [[Golden Lions]] 1996\u201397\n* [[Lions (Super rugby franchise)|Lions]] 1998\u20132002\n\n===South Africa national rugby union team===\nHe played his first test match for the [[South Africa national rugby union team|Springboks]] on 23 July [[1994 in sports|1994]] against [[New Zealand national rugby union team|New Zealand]] (lost 13-9).\n\n==Honours==\n\n===Provincial===\n* [[Currie Cup]] winner in 1993.\n* [[Super Rugby|Super 10]] winner in 1993.\n\n===South Africa national rugby union team===\n* 34 caps\n* 6 tries (30 points).\n* Caps by year : 4 in [[1994 in sports|1994]], 8 in [[1995 in sports|1995]], 11 in [[1996 in sports|1996]], 2 in [[1997 in sports|1997]], 4 in [[1999 in sports|1999]], 3 in [[2000 in sports|2000]], 2 in [[2001 in sports|2001]].\n\n===World Cup===\n* 1995 : World Champions, 4 caps, ([[Australia national rugby union team|Wallabies]], [[Samoa national rugby union team|Samoa]], [[France national rugby union team|France]], [[New Zealand national rugby union team|All Blacks]]).\n* 1999 : missed with an injury sustained against [[New Zealand national rugby union team|All Blacks]] in [[Dunedin]].\n\n===Other caps===\n* Springboks A International (in 1994).\n* Student international.\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20131216155221/http://www.genslin.us/bokke/SARugby.html Springboks in 1996]\n*[http://statistics.scrum.com/rugby_stats_05.asp?ID=ZMU6 scrum.com statistics]\n\n{{South Africa Squad 1995 World Cup}}\n{{Portal bar|Sport}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Mulder, Japie}}\n[[Category:1969 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People convicted of attempted rape]]\n[[Category:People convicted of indecent assault]]\n[[Category:South African rugby union players]]\n[[Category:South Africa international rugby union players]]\n[[Category:Rugby union centres]]\n[[Category:Golden Lions players]]\n[[Category:Lions (Super Rugby) players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Use South African English|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox rugby biography\n|                   name = \n|                  image =\n|                caption = \n|              birth_name = \n|               nickname = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1969|10|18}}\n| birth_place = [[Springs, South Africa|Springs]], [[South Africa]]\n| height = {{height|m=1.84}}\n| weight = 84 kg (13 st 3 lb; 185 lb)\n|            ru_position = [[Centre (rugby union)|Centre]]\n|        ru_amateuryears = \n|        ru_amateurclubs = \n|            ru_amupdate = \n|        ru_nationalteam = [[South Africa national rugby union team|South Africa]]\n|       ru_nationalyears = 1994-2001\n|        ru_nationalcaps = 34\n|      ru_nationalpoints = (35)\n|            ru_ntupdate = 26 June 2015\n|           ru_clubyears = \n|            ru_proclubs =\n|            ru_clubcaps = \n|          ru_clubpoints = \n|          ru_clubupdate = \n|                super14 = \n|           super14years = \n|            super14caps =  \n|          super14points = \n|         ru_currentclub = \n|          super14update = \n|            ru_province =\n|      